derivation.yuyuan_name: mid 16th cent.: from French compartiment, from Italian compartimento, from compartire, from late Latin compartiri 'divide'

entry.def: A compartment is one of the separate spaces into which a railway carriage is divided.

example.ex: On the way home we shared our first class compartment with a group of businessmen.
example.tran: 回家的路上，我们和一群生意人一起坐在一等车厢。

entry.def: A compartment is one of the separate parts of an object that is used for keeping things in.

example.ex: I put a bottle of champagne in the freezer compartment.
example.tran: 我把一瓶香槟放进冷冻室。

example.ex: ...the secret compartment of my jewel box.

means.word_mean: 1. a small space or subdivision for storage
2. a partitioned section or separate room within a larger enclosed area
